title: animbook
text: stage, first need transform data categorized format. function calculate scaling based argument user provided. data needs contain following variable function work: data: dbl_change, data frame contained numerical values. id: id, needs factor variable. values: values, needs numeric variable. time: time, needs integer variable. also additional options allow user customize. group: column name distinguishes values group. ncat: number categories created scaling values. breaks: vector creating bins. label: vector provide label qtile. group_scaling: column name used grouping variable scaling. scaling: scaling method. function can calculate four different scales using options. function return categorized data.
code: categorized_dbl <- anim_prep(data = dbl_change,                               id = id,                               values = values,                              time = time) # rank scaling rank_scaling <- anim_prep(data = dbl_change,                               id = id,                               values = values,                              time = time)  # absolute scaling absolute_scaling <- anim_prep(data = dbl_change,                               id = id,                               values = values,                              time = time,                              scaling = "absolute")  # rank scaling by group rank_group_scaling <- anim_prep(data = dbl_change,                               id = id,                               values = values,                              time = time,                              group_scaling = gp)  # absolute scaling by group absolute_group_scaling <- anim_prep(data = dbl_change,                               id = id,                               values = values,                              time = time,                              group_scaling = gp,                              scaling = "absolute")  rank_scaling #> # A tibble: 400 × 4 #>    id     time qtile label #>    <fct> <int> <int> <chr> #>  1 1      2020     3 3     #>  2 2      2020     2 2     #>  3 3      2020     4 4     #>  4 4      2020     3 3     #>  5 5      2020     2 2     #>  6 6      2020     2 2     #>  7 7      2020     4 4     #>  8 8      2020     4 4     #>  9 9      2020     3 3     #> 10 10     2020     4 4     #> # ℹ 390 more rows

title: animbook
text: preparing data, can now plot . three plots available package: kangaroo, plots observation’s movement time. wallaby, subset plot either top bottom see group observational period. funnel_web_spider, faceted plot time variable.    kangaroo wallaby plots can animated using function next stage. funnel_web_spider supported static plot. can also choose whether want animate plot using gganimate plotly.
code: dbl_categorized <- anim_prep(data = dbl_change,                               id = id,                               values = values,                              time = time,                              group = gp)  # kangaroo plot kangaroo_plot(dbl_categorized) #> You can now use the animbook::anim_animate() function to #>           transform it into an animated object # wallaby plot wallaby_plot(dbl_categorized) #> You can now use the animbook::anim_animate() function to #>           transform it into an animated object # funnel web spider plot funnel_web_plot(dbl_categorized)
